Summary report 2017

UKMON

July 09 2017

## [1] "Dataset: ALL period 2017-01-02 to 2017-05-27"

Summary of activity

In 2017 a total of 24 cameras contributed data to the UKMON repository. Together, these cameras recorded 8970 individual meteor observations. The number of recorded observations by station is as follows:

After applying quality criteria we found that 1399 meteors were observed by more than one camera (Unified observations). The following shows a count of the number of meters observed by two, three, etc. cameras.

The number of unified observations as a percentage of individual observations is 15.6%. A breakdown of unified observation counts by stream (top ten) is as follows:

Magnitudes

The following graphs show the distribution of magnitudes:

The following plots shows the altitude of the atart and end of ablation for each individual meteor. The plot is in order of decreasing start height and gives a good visualisation of the depth of the ablation zone. Where in the atmosphere ablation occurs will depend on factors such as meteor velocity and composition.

The maximum observed altitude was 162.2 km and the minimum observed altitude was 42.4 km. The distribution of distances travelled through the ablation zone was as follows:
